40|$|Naga Industry is {{a family}} company which is produce plastic mechine product. The purpose of this company is optimalize the profit and sales the product in many city or country. Based on {{the purpose of this}} company to grow the bussines, Naga Industry need to change from {{traditional}} system to modern system which is suitable with <b>accounting</b> <b>principle.</b> The purpose of this research is to knowing the calculation of cost of good sold for Dys PP 21 is suitable with <b>Accounting</b> <b>Principle</b> and job order costing theory. The research method used in this study is comparative analysis by comparing between <b>accounting</b> <b>principle</b> theory and the company calcutaion doing by Naga Industry. The result of this research are job order costing theory is not applied by Naga Industry who is using order system to produce the product and cause underestimate of cost of good sold. An underestimate of this calculation cause margin constribution which have been forcested cannot be reach. The conclusion of this study are Accounting Priciple is not applied by Naga Industry as individual company which is not important for the managerial. The result of this study has become a base for writer to give some suggestion to Naga Industry to use <b>accounting</b> <b>principle</b> in their own daily company activiy because this is very important to produce the right calculation of cost of good sold...|$|R
40|$|The thesis {{describes}} {{questions of}} exchange differences {{in accordance with}} Czech generally <b>accounting</b> <b>principle</b> and {{in accordance with the}} International financial reporting standards. Accordance with Czech <b>accounting</b> <b>principle</b> is the choice of the exchange rate and method of evaluating and accounting for exchange rate differences. The second part of this thesis is focused on International financial reporting standards. It explains the concept of functional currency factors and its determination. It describes translation from the local currency to the functional currency and the translation from the functional currency to the presentation currency. The last part of thesis describes the functional currency in US GAAP...|$|R
